19 city or county took action inconsistent with, or in violation of, G.S. 160D-108(b) or
20 G.S. 143-755, the court shall award reasonable attorneys' fees and costs to the party who
21 successfully challenged the local government's failure to comply with any of those provisions.
22 (c) In all other matters, matters not covered by subsection (a) or (b) of this section, the
23 court may award reasonable attorneys' fees and costs to the prevailing private litigant.
